    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>Data regarding coronavirus disease (COVID-19) infection complications among people with HIV (PWH) are expanding but sometimes conflicting. This report presents the results of a retrospective review of 103 patients at a single urban academic health center with confirmed severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2) infection. The study showed that hospitalization is related to host factors such as age 65 years or older with an increasing number of specific non-communicable disease comorbidities, and not to HIV-attributable factors.</jats:p>",
